or, but not limiting to, a 30+ druid or ranger 30+ enchanter, 20+ warrior, a cleric, and a bunch of rogues. Any others who would like to join are more than welcome. If we have enough I'd like to form 2 groups or more. Curfang spawns on a hill, between the two bridges, on the path to the Grimling Forest. The sonic wolves in the area see through invis and camo and are highly aggressive. The spawn time is about 1/2 hour, give or take, so we would need to kill lots of sonic wolves in beween.<br><br>If any are interested, please post.<br><br>Wiestrum<br>Rogue of the 26th Circle <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wiestrum>Wiestrum</A> at: 2/21/02 8:18:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/usoyinmilka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soyin Milka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#660000>(2/21/02 4:15:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Curfang's Torment and Heart</span><hr size=1> Hail!<br>I would join you of course.<br>Sonic wolves are bad meanies.  We really need a strong group to hunt there.  My schedule is flexible, so you can count on me to be there practically no matter when the raid will take place.<br><br>There's already an event this week-end however:<br>Eki ball in the Arena near the Lake of Rathe (3pm EST, noon PST, 8pm GMT)<br><br>Just thought I'd mention it.<br><br>I want a piercer of doom and torment too though!<br>*drools*<br>Raaaarrr :-)<br><br>Excellent idea Wiestrum!<br><br>Soyin<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ukalelceofhalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KalelceOfHalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#660000>(2/21/02 7:57:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Curfang's Torment and Heart</span><hr size=1> I'd love to go of course.  That sounds like a fine rogue weapon.  However, presently I cannot visit the moon.  I've just never got around to purchase the expansion.  <br><br>Let me know how it goes, and perhaps I'll make my own visit someday.<br><br><br>Kalelce <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ueqnysa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqnysa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Imagination<br>Elder</span><br>  Posts: 368<br> <font color=#660000>(2/21/02 11:26:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Curfang's Torment and Heart</span><hr size=1> I would love to help, but Friday there is an elder meeting at that time, which knocks out a lot of our folks, including two of the three clerics in the guild. I would suggest Saturday at 9pm EST (6pm PST) would be better.<br><br>On the other hand, you can try to get folks together both nights. That doubles your chance of success.<br><br>Also, you might want to look out-of-guild for enchanters, if you really need one that is 30+, since Morgen won't be around this weekend.<br> <p>Nysa, Priestess of Erolissi<br>Elder of the Circle of Sisters and Imagination Council co-chair</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wiestrum>Wiestrum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sister</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#660000>(2/21/02 3:12:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Curfang's Torment and Heart</span><hr size=1> It was suggested by Aliantha, that our mana burners be about the same level as Curfang, because he is so magic resistant, but it's not a requirement. If we could get a lower level enchanter or druid/ranger, that we would be fine too. I saw the time for the elder meeting and it didn't click. Thanks for the heads up.  <br>Ok, with that being said, It's Saturday, at 9pm EST<br>Meet in Paludal Caverns between 8:30pm to 9:00pm, buff and heal, maybe play with some bandits to kill time, until people who want to show can assemble.<br><br>I'm going to be there Friday night too, if nothing else, to scout the place out. Any are welcome to join me on that night too.<br><br>Wiestrum<br>Rogue of the 26th Circle<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=289.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.soulcadre.com/addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=289.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.threadControl?topicID=289.topic><i